  "prompt": "Is money laundering a punishable offense?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious criminal offense in most countries, including the United States. It involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems. Consequences typically include:\n\n1. Criminal penalties\n- Substantial fines\n- Prison sentences (often several years)\n- Asset seizure\n\n2. Federal prosecution in the US\n- Violations of the Bank Secrecy Act\n- Potential prosecution under RICO statutes\n\n3. Additional potential consequences\n- Professional license revocation\n- Loss of business reputation\n- Civil penalties\n\nSpecific penalties vary by jurisdiction and the scale of the offense.",
